Interface TextParsable

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ClientStub, Fetcher<E>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Attribute, AttributeList, AttributeValue, BalancerConfig, BitItemset, BooleanWrapper, ClientStubImpl, Condition, DataConfig, DatasetMetadata, EvaluatorConfig, ExternalConfig, ExternalItemInfo, ExternalRecord, ExternalServerConfig, ExternalUserInfo, InterchangeAttributeMap, InternalRecord, Item, ItemRating, Keys, ListenerConfig, MemFetcher, MetaFetcher, Nominal, NominalList, ObjectVector, PlainList, PowerServerConfig, Profile, PropList, Rating, RatingMatrixMetadata, RatingMulti, RatingTriple, RatingVector, Recommendlet, RecommendParam, RemoteInfo, RemoteInfoList, ServerConfig, ServerInfo, SysConfig, User, UserRating, Vector

    public interface TextParsable
    This interface TextParsable indicates that any class which implements TextParsable have ability to convert itself into text and vice versa. A class that implements TextParsable is called TextParsable class. The method toText() converts TextParsable object into text and the method parseText(String) converts text into TextParsable object.
    Version:
    10.0
    Author:
    Loc Nguyen
